article.headline: Monmouth (N.J.) 74, Wagner 58
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- John Bunch scored 19 points to lead Monmouth to a 74-58 victory over Wagner on Monday night. Dejan Delic, Marques Alston and Whitney Coleman each added 10 points for the Hawks (12-11, 9-3 Northeast Conference), who won their third straight. Durell Vinson had 19 points for the Seahawks (10-10, 3-8), who have lost four in a row. DeEarnest McLemore and Joey Mundweiler each added 12 points for Wagner. Bunch had all but two of the points in a 13-4 run that gave the Hawks a 20-12 lead midway through the first half. Consecutive 3-pointers by Matt Vitale and Mundweiler got the Seahawks within 29-27 with 4:44 left, but a 3 by Alston capped a 7-0 run for the Hawks, who went on to lead 38-31 at halftime. Bunch's jumper capped an 8-0 run that gave Monmouth a 49-33 lead with 14:16 to play in the game.
